# ── TURN / STUN Server Configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────
# These variables configure the WebRTC TURN server used for video calls.
# TURN is required for users behind strict NAT/firewalls (e.g. corporate networks).
#
# Development default: The app automatically falls back to the free openrelay.metered.ca
# TURN server if these are not set. This is fine for local testing.
#
# Production: Replace with your own TURN server (Twilio, Metered.ca, Coturn, etc.)
# See: https://www.metered.ca/stun-turn  or  https://www.twilio.com/docs/stun-turn

# Full TURN URL — can be turn:, turns:, or a ?transport=tcp variant
# VITE_TURN_URL=turn:your-turn-server.example.com:3478

# Credentials for the TURN server
# VITE_TURN_USERNAME=your_username
# VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=your_password
